ec37f531-f636-4b80-8756-517d82f489f8.29f8b9d2-41f2-4b33-9c1c-f1f94c86a864.description=
Iterates through a list of values. If the list changes while running, the updates will be appended to the list.

Inputs\:
separator - The list separator (or delimiter).
list - The list to be split

Responses\:
has more - Another value was in the list, and has been returned.
failure - failed to process the list.
no more - The iterator has gone fully through the list. This response will only be returned once per iteration through the list, a subsequent call to the Iterator will restart the Iteration through the list.

Returns\:
The current element of the list, if the response is has more
ec37f531-f636-4b80-8756-517d82f489f8.2a38d5dc-1901-4a93-b47b-a559eecbe1f7.description=
Adds a flow variable into the local context (available to itself and child flows only)

Input Parameters\:
keyName - the name of the flow variable to use
myValue - the value to assign the flow variable

Responses\:
success - assigned the flow variable

Scriptlet Example\:
[$scriptletContext putGlobal\: $keyName, $myValue];
ec37f531-f636-4b80-8756-517d82f489f8.309a8f24-8985-46d0-9c36-d6b4e43e8bdb.prompt=IP Address or DNS name of the SA Web Service. ec37f531-f636-4b80-8756-517d82f489f8.45478bbe-f354-43a2-b486-5f15c1aeedc9.description=
This is an operation that does nothing. It can be used for filtering flow variables by feeding them in as inputs and filtering them on the results tab.

Inputs\:
field1 - optional input that can be used for filtering flow variables.
field2 - optional input that can be used for filtering flow variables.
field3 - optional input that can be used for filtering flow variables.
field4 - optional input that can be used for filtering flow variables.

Responses\:
success - this operation never fails.
ec37f531-f636-4b80-8756-517d82f489f8.4abb8f2c-1cec-48b4-88d5-551e550fcf56.description=
Check to see if the value stored in a specified flow variable, denoted by key, is null.

Inputs\:
keyName - The key to check, i.e. the name of the flow variable.

Returns\: 
The value in the specified key, i.e. flow variable.

Responses\:
isNull - If the key is a null pointer, i.e. the flow variable doesn't have an assigned value.
notNull - If some value is stored in the key, i.e the flow variable has a value assigned.
ec37f531-f636-4b80-8756-517d82f489f8.4d326ee8-7456-41b5-9920-d05df74c6f2d.prompt=ADM Name of ADM Application TargetTier. ec37f531-f636-4b80-8756-517d82f489f8.672ace9a-325a-4af2-b638-92e204dc60f6.prompt=ADM Name of ADM Application Target. ec37f531-f636-4b80-8756-517d82f489f8.68b4125c-1d24-453e-a015-e4273242e81c.prompt=Username of the SA. ec37f531-f636-4b80-8756-517d82f489f8.8af45f92-49ca-4dfc-88ff-1ac40bcda90a.description=This operation retrieves the details of TargetTiers for the given Target managed in ADM. If TargetTier name is not given then all the TargetTiers for the given Target will be reported. NOTE\: Value of each output variable will be separated by ',' when more than one TargetTiers is reported. This Operation is supported for SA 9.0 or later. Inputs\: coreHost - IP Address or DNS name of the SA Web Service. corePort - HTTP(S) port of SA Web Service. By default it is '443' coreProtocol - HTTP / HTTPS. By default it is 'HTTPS' coreUsername - Username of the SA. corePassword - Password of SA user. coreVersion - [Optional] SA version. By default, it is the SA version being used. admEnvironment - ADM Name of ADM Application Environment. admTarget - ADM Name of ADM Application Target. admTargetTier - [Optional] ADM Name of ADM Application TargetTier. Outputs\: status - Operation completion Status. idAdmTargetTier - ADM Id of Application TargetTier. admTargetTier - ADM Name of ADM Application TargetTier. server - Name of the SA managed server. It may have more than one server separated by ';'. Responses\: success - Operation passed. For more details, see the output parameter 'status'. failure - Operation failed. For more details, see the output parameter 'status' and 'exception'. ec37f531-f636-4b80-8756-517d82f489f8.9c38a7da-2cf4-40ac-a1aa-80b750e3674f.prompt=Password of SA user. ec37f531-f636-4b80-8756-517d82f489f8.a90bc239-c7c8-4768-af3f-40e6fd3c00c7.prompt=ADM Name of ADM Application Environment. ec37f531-f636-4b80-8756-517d82f489f8.description=
Get the Server Id attached to a Target Tier from the List of Server Ids

Inputs\:
coreHost - the Core host of the ADM 
coreUsername - user name to connect to Core
corePassword - the password to connect to Core
artifactId - Component Id of Application Tier.
userIdentifier - OO Application UUID to authorize REST Call
serverIds - List of Server Component Ids
admEnvironment - ADM Name of ADM Application Environment.
admTarget - ADM Name of ADM Application Target.
admEnvironment -  ADM Environment Name of ADM Application.



Responses\:
success - if the command completes execution and its exit code is 0
failure - otherwise

Returns
server - Fully Qualified Domain Name of the Server in the Core in the Target Tier
serverId - Corresponding Server Id
